<section id="about" class="section wrap" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-title">About</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I’m drawn to problems where <strong>data, money, and global scale</strong>
      meet: streaming and batch pipelines, workflow orchestration across
      long-running jobs, configuration that must stay consistent across
      partitions and regions, and on-call tooling that makes failures
      diagnosable. On <strong>Bedrock Commerce</strong>, that shows up as
      metering, allocation, and settlement workflows that have to stay
      accurate through model launches, region expansion, and hard operational
      deadlines.
    </p>
    <p>
      I’ve been at <strong>Amazon for nine years and counting</strong>. I
      spend a lot of time on <strong>architecture reviews, design docs,
      and mentoring</strong> — turning ambiguous requirements into systems
      with clear failure modes and measurable behavior. Earlier, I built
      and operated <strong>Amazon Kinesis Video Streams</strong> control
      and data-plane features, including public AWS APIs and
      fleet-wide infrastructure change under strict availability targets.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of work I’m a <strong>dog person</strong> (golden retriever,
      <strong>Splash</strong>), a parent to a <strong>three-year-old</strong>,
      and I reset with <strong>racquetball</strong>, <strong>Seattle-area
      hiking</strong>, summer walks, <strong>books</strong>, and
      <strong>travel</strong> when I can.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

